# Always publish — LAN and Vercel

When you finish a user-facing change (feature, fix, seed that affects demo/gameplay):

1. Commit the chunk locally (commit-as-you-go).
2. Keep / refresh the LAN stack (`npm run dev:lan` / LaunchAgent `com.havenpm.dev-lan` on **http://10.0.0.230:3000** or the Mac’s current LAN IP) so local party play stays current.
3. **Push to `main`** and **deploy with `npx vercel --prod --yes`** in the same turn — do not ask “publish?” and do not wait for confirmation.
4. Confirm the deploy aliased to https://haven-pm.vercel.app (or report failure).
5. Only skip push/deploy if the change is purely local tooling with no app impact, or the user explicitly says not to publish this one.

Request approval when required for protected `main` / production deploy tooling; still attempt publish rather than stopping after a local-only commit.
